iTerm 2
Solarized Color Settings

Installation:

Download current build of iTerm 2 from:
http://sites.google.com/site/iterm2home/

NOTE: Only builds 480 (Jan 11 2011) and later support import of color schemes.  
If the stable release doesn't include this function, grab the nightly build 
from:

http://code.google.com/p/iterm2/downloads/list

Open iTerm 2, open Preferences, click on the "Addresses" (formerly Bookmarks) 
icon in the preferences toolbar, then select the "colors" tab. Click on the 
"load presets" and select "import...". Select the Solaris Light or Dark theme 
file.

